Nvidia shares were slipping 0.1% at $181.43 in premarket trading. headline: Trump’s Pay-For-Play Chips Deal Generates Alarm and Optimism
summary: Experts and people familiar with the matter said the surprise deal, in which Nvidia Corp. and Advanced Micro Devices Inc. agreed to pay 15% of their revenues from Chinese AI chip sales to the US, potentially provides a path to enter the Chinese market despite severe export controls, tariffs and other trade barriers.  The question that companies must now confront is whether the risk is worth taking.
